Four carats is the weight where I stop recommending buyers push for higher color grades. At this size, the bow-tie effect, the L/W ratio, and the setting choice matter far more than whether you're at G or F. I've seen $114,000 D-VVS1 stones look dull because the proportions were wrong, and $63,000 G-VS2 stones stop people in their tracks because the cut was exceptional. At 4ct, always ask for the Idealscope image. That image tells you more than the grading report.
