## My Final Verdict

**Natural 4ct oval:** The G-VS2 at [$63,247](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29156834?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the only defensible spend. Budget $65,000–$67,000 all-in with a double pavé or twisted vine setting. Anything above F is prestige tax that no eye will validate. Request the Idealscope before buying — bow-tie is the 4ct killer.

**Lab 4ct oval:** The D-IF IGI at [$10,284](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28561497?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is extraordinary. Total budget under $12,000. The $52,963 Lab Divide makes 4ct the single most compelling weight to go lab in this entire series — the savings are enough to buy a house deposit in some markets.

**Between 3ct and 4ct:** The 4ct Rarity Premium is real — $13,954/ct versus $12,294/ct at 3ct. If your budget sits between $40,000–$55,000, a 3ct natural in a beautiful setting with money left over is objectively better value than stretching into the 4ct entry tier.

